        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The date is established by CD’s annotation.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_8276.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Lawford Maclean Acland</ref> was Harrison’s nephew. Harrison had probably been commenting on the Darwins’ grandson, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1206.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Bernard Darwin</ref>, who lived with the Darwins. CD had discussed elephants’ tears in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref>, pp. 167–8 and n. 20. The information in this letter was not added to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2401.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi> 2d ed.</ref>, edited by <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1222.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Francis Darwin</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_8277.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">John Harrison</ref> was Ellen’s husband.</note>
        </div>        
            
